sabre corporation  wikipedia sabre corporation from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search sabre corporation type public traded as nasdaq sabr sp  component industry travel technology travel services founded   headquarters southlake texas united states key people lawrence kellner executive chairman sean menke president and ceo products tripcase getthere sabre airline solutions sabre travel network sabre hospitality solutions revenue us billion  operating income us million  net income us million  total assets us billion  total equity us million  number of employees around   website wwwsabrecom sabre corporation is a travel technology company based in southlake texas it is the largest global distribution systems provider for air bookings in north america american airlines founded the company in  and it was spun off in  texas pacific group and silver lake partners acquired sabre in  sabre began publicly trading on the nasdaq in  sabre hospitality solutions an it solutions provider is the companys largest growing division contents  history  early history  s  operations  businesses  acquisitions  references  external links historyedit early historyedit in  cr smith the president of american airlines met blair smith an ibm salesman on a flight and developed the sabre the semiautomatic business research environment concept the system was based on sage the first major system to use interactive realtime computing which ibm had developed for military use sabre corporation was founded in  by american airlines sabre corporation installed the first sabre reservation system in briarcliff manor new york that year the system consisted of two ibm  mainframe computers and processed  calls per day in  sabres nationwide network was completed and became the largest commercial realtime dataprocessing system in the world sabre corporation handled  passenger reservations per hour in  the sabre system upgraded to ibm s and moved to a new center in tulsa oklahoma in  in  the sabre system was installed into a travel agency for the first time this allowed travel agents to have instant access to flights by the end of the year  locations installed the sabre system sabre introduced bargainfinder the industrys first automated lowfare search capability in  the following year easysabre was launched it gave consumers with personal computers access to the sabre system to make airline hotel and car rental reservations in  the company launched travelocity an online travel agency sabre formed a joint venture with abacus international in  to create the sabresonic passenger solution a customized version of sabres reservations system to abacus subscribers in asia sedit amr corporation the parent company of american airlines spun off its controlling stake in sabre corporation in  to form an independent company the following year sabre began migrating its old mainframe for air travel shopping and pricing to hp nonstop and linux servers in  the company acquired lastminutecom an online travel and leisure retailer texas pacific group and silver lake partners acquired sabre corporation in march  in march  the company acquired calidris a revenue integrity and business intelligence solutions company sabre corporation acquired softhotel a webbased property management solutions provider in june  the company launched sabre red app centre in march  in april  sabre corporation went public on nasdaq under the ticker symbol sabr the ipo sold for  per share and valued sabre at  billion the company acquired genares a hospitality technology company that september in december  bravofly rumbo group acquired sabre european online travel agency lastminutecom in january  sabre sold its travelocity brand to expedia inc for  million in july  sabre acquired abacus international a global distribution system based in the asiapacific region the deal included longterm distribution agreements between sabre and the  asian airlines that previously shared ownership of abacus in june  sabre announced tom klein would be resigning as ceo by the end of  operationsedit the company is based in southlake texas and has additional offices in london kraków bangalore montevideo and buenos aires in december  the company handled approximately  data transactions every second for customers according to the fort worth startelegram at the time the company did business with  airlines and  hotels it operates under the platforms travel network airline and hospitality solutions businessesedit getthere sabre airline solutions sabre travel network sabre hospitality solutions tripcase acquisitionsedit preview travel  dillion communication systems  gradient solutions  getthere  sabre pacific  nexion inc  david r bornemann associates  site  resfeber scandinavia  kiehl hendrickson group  axsresource airport resource management solutions  world choice travel  rm rocade  showticketscom  synxis corporation  southwest travel systems  igougocom  lastminutecom  esite marketing  flight explorer  eb   calidris   flightline data services   fwz  softhotel  prism   genares   abacus international  trust international  referencesedit  httpwwwmarketwatchcominvestingstocksabrfinancials  httpwwwmarketwatchcominvestingstocksabrfinancials  httpwwwmarketwatchcominvestingstocksabrfinancials  httpwwwmarketwatchcominvestingstocksabrfinancials  httpwwwmarketwatchcominvestingstocksabrfinancials  httpinvestorssabrecomsecfilingcfmfilingidcik  chris ciaccia  april  travelocity owner sabre holdings returns to wall street after ipo retrieved  november    a b c lance murray  april  sabre holdings sets ipo valuation at up to b retrieved  november    david baum december  flying high with a private database cloud retrieved  november    a b travelocity owner sabres ipo prices at  per share underwriter  april  retrieved  november    a b c american airlines assails sabre in databusiness trial  october  retrieved  november    a b tpg and silver lake take sabre private  april  retrieved  november    a b c s