l drivers for airline revenue growth and those experiences represent heavy influences on product investments from suppliers intermediaries and software vendors to help ensure customer loyalty travel suppliers are also investing in advanced analytics to understand customer traits behaviors and preferences to support customer acquisition maximize revenuegeneration potential from the customer base and retain the most profitable customers to enable customers with targeted options nextgeneration applications collect information from customers in realtime analytics have advanced from descriptive analytics to predictive analytics in other words what will happen to prescriptive analytics recommending options targeted content a common theme across the travel value chain is to display targeted content to a given customer based on implicit or explicit information that is known about the customer this type of deep understanding can be derived from alternate data sources such as transactional booking and ticketing data demographic data social media survey data and other sources to segment and target customers with relevant offers segmentation of customers based on purchasebehavior patterns is never perfect and should be refined on a periodic basis as there are new data sources and as customer behaviors change over time in the competitive marketplace travel solutions should focus on products that resonate with customers to improve conversion rates and maximize revenues for suppliers with every interaction by offering the ideal product or bundle to a customer at the right price when he or she is ready to make a purchase based on customerbehavior data read the full article here airlinesascendaviation ben vinod ben is sabres chief scientist he focuses on innovation in travel and transportation primarily through advanced decision support and analytics capabilities for suppliers airlines hotels rental car cruise line ferry and distribution global distribution systems online travel agencies see more articles from this author » older newer related articles blog jul   a new decision support tool for managing airline frequent flyers retailing  merchandising blog jul   irregular operations planning for the unplanned to recover operations efficiently airlines blog jun   expanding capabilities for group travelers introducing airvision group optimizer airlines blog jun   is your airline’s technology making efficient crew recovery impossible it shouldn’t airlines blog jun   the pride of greece a conversation with dimitrios gerogiannis ceo of aegean airlines airlines blog may   the digital experience giving airline customers a truly digital experience airlines blog may   travel expert index on the airline passenger experience around the industry blog may   the incredible power of placing the traveler at the center of the airport experience airlines sign me up for insights sign up for the email we promise we won’t share your email address with anyone email address about careers news  insights investor relations is your airline’s technology making efficient crew recovery impossible it shouldn’t « sabre search sabrecom what we do businesses sabre airline solutions sabre hospitality solutions sabre travel network technologies data solutions mobile online commerce platform services software who we serve airlines  airports car rental companies corporations cruise lines developers government hotels meta search engines online travel agencies rail carriers tour companies travel agencies travel consolidators travel management companies news  insights newsroom press releases insights blog research  intelligence innovation hub labs events about executive leadership corporate responsibility locations contact us privacy policy copyright  trademark careers people  culture university recruiting total rewards growth  learning investor relations financial releases events  presentations corporate governance financials  filings stock information contact investor relations sh