minimizing cancellations and additional crew costs an optimizationbased decisionsupport system can greatly assist airline coordinators in producing better recovery solutions with substantial savings and improved passenger experience sabre aircentre recovery manager crew has been designed and implemented to help airlines solve complex crewrecovery problems through the combination of experience and the latest operationsresearch advancements the nextgeneration product is based on a holistic optimization approach to generate deployable crew rosters significantly improving an airline’s response time to disruptions as well as reducing operational costs success during severe storms in  and  record snowfalls hammered the northeastern region of the united states resulting in large cancellation packages for airlines operating in the area an especially severe blizzard which was given the name “winter storm juno” by meteorologists hit north america in january  the storm produced record levels of snowfall causing one of the largest totals of flight cancellations in history january  also happened to be the effective date for far federal aviation regulations part  in the united states which effectively imposed stricter crew flight and duty limitations as well as higher crew rest requirements such rule changes considerably increase the complexity of rescheduling crewmembers during disruptions dealing with this complex task recovery manager crew was successful in helping airlines recover  percent of disrupted crew schedules for all of the storms within the same day the endtoend process using the solution was  times faster than the typical airline process and it provided reduced disruption impact to passengers by providing crew to every flight possible quality of life for crewmembers was also improved due to faster communication and a lower number of unplanned flights successful realworld utilization of recovery manager crew during these storms produced further innovative ideas which have been incorporated in the process of continual system enhancement with the primary focus on improving solution quality usability and speed read the full article ramakrishna thiruveedhi and chunhua gao are members of operatons research team at sabre airline solutions they can be contacted at ramakrishnathiruveedhisabrecom and chunhuagaosabrecom airline operationsairlinesaviation ramakrishna thiruveedhi ramakrishna works in operations research at sabre airline solutions where he uses his background as a data scientist to implement decisionmaking algorithms see more articles from this author » older newer related articles blog jul   a new decision support tool for managing airline frequent flyers retailing  merchandising blog jul   irregular operations planning for the unplanned to recover operations efficiently airlines blog jul   customercentric sales how to maximize sales through better product distribution airlines blog jun   expanding capabilities for group travelers introducing airvision group optimizer airlines blog jun   the pride of greece a conversation with dimitrios gerogiannis ceo of aegean airlines airlines blog may   travel expert index on the airline passenger experience around the industry blog may   the evolution of airline revenue management defining the next generation approach airlines blog may   the incredible power of placing the traveler at the center of the airport experience airlines sign me up for insights sign up for the email we promise we won’t share your email address with anyone email address about careers news  insights investor relations buy pepper spray online  sabre you could win acollege scholarshipfrom tell me more no thanks skip to main content the  brand used by police worldwide login create account  items  fulltext search apply toggle navigation pepper spray and personal safety products on the go seniors athletic home defense students  parents inert pepper sprays tactical products supporting charity personal security alarms