travel consolidators travel management companies careers people  culture university recruiting total rewards growth  learning news  insights newsroom press releases insights blog research  intelligence innovation hub labs events about executive leadership locations contact us corporate responsibility investor relations privacy policy copyright  trademark search sabrecom blog is your airline’s technology making efficient crew recovery impossible it shouldn’t by ramakrishna thiruveedhi on  jun  airlines agencies  otas airlines around the industry corporate travel culture data  analytics developers  startups hotels mobility research retailing  merchandising travel trends traveler experience more newsroom press contacts logo usage press releases insights blog airlines hotels agencies  otas corporate travel developers  startups data  analytics retailing mobility traveler experience culture industry  public affairs research  intelligence innovation hub labs events the capability of airlines to quickly and efficiently recover crew from disruptions and get their rosters back on schedule is one of the most critical factors necessary to succeed in the air transport marketplace a nextgeneration crewrecovery solution incorporating the best and latest advancements in technology provides faster and better disruption management to airlines during disruptions airlines are faced with the problem of recovering crew schedules and providing an adequate number of crewmembers for each flight airline crew coordinators have a primary critical objective to reassign crews while minimizing cancellations and additional crew costs an optimizationbased decisionsupport system can greatly assist airline coordinators in producing better recovery solutions with substantial savings and improved passenger experience sabre aircentre recovery manager crew has been designed and implemented to help airlines solve complex crewrecovery problems through the combination of experience and the latest operationsresearch advancements the nextgeneration product is based on a holistic optimization approach to generate deployable crew rosters significantly improving an airline’s response time to disruptions as well as reducing operational costs success during severe storms in  and  record snowfalls hammered the northeastern region of the united states resulting in large cancellation packages for airlines operating in the area an especially severe blizzard which was given the name “winter storm juno” by meteorologists hit north america in january  the storm produced record levels of snowfall causing one of the largest totals of flight cancellations in history january  also happened to be the effective date for far federal aviation regulations part  in the united states which effectively imposed stricter crew flight and duty limitations as well as higher crew rest requirements such rule changes considerably increase the complexity of rescheduling crewmembers during disruptions dealing with this complex task recovery manager crew was successful in helping airlines recover  percent of disrupted crew schedules for all of the storms within the same day the endtoend process using the solution was  times faster than the typical airline process and it provided reduced disruption impact to passengers by providing crew to every flight possible quality of life for crewmembers was also improved due to faster communication and a lower number of unplanned flights successful realworld utilization of recovery manager crew during these storms produced further innovative ideas which have been incorporated in the process of continual system enhancement with the primary focus on improving solution quality usability and speed read the full article ramakrishna thiruveedhi and chunhua gao are members of operatons research team at sabre airline solutions they can be contacted at ramakrishnathiruveedhisabrecom and chunhuagaosabrecom airline operationsairlinesaviation ramakrishna thiruveedhi ramakrishna works in operations research at sabre airline solutions where he uses his background as a data scientist to implement decisionmaking algorithms see more articles from this author » older newer related articles blog jul   a new decision support tool for managing airline frequent flyers retailing  merchandising blog jul   irregular operations planning for the unplanned to recover operations efficiently airlines blog jul   customercentric sales how to maximize sales through better product distribution airlines blog jun   expanding capabilities for group travelers introducing airvision group optimizer airlines blog jun   the pride of greece a conversation with dimitrios gerogiannis ceo of aegean airlines airlines blog may   travel expert index on the airline passenger experience around the industry blog may   the evolution of airline revenue management defining the next generation approach airlines blog may   the incredible power of placing the traveler at the center of the airport experience airlines sign me up for insights sign up for the email we promise we won’t share your email address with anyone email address about careers news  insights investor relations travel expert index on managing expectations and improving the business travel experience « sabre search sabrecom what we do businesses sabre airline solutions sabre hospitality solutions sabre travel network technologies data solutions mobile online commerce platform services software who we serve airlines  airports car rental companies corporations cruise lines developers government hotels meta search engines online travel agencies rail carriers tour companies travel agencies travel consolidators travel management companies news  insights newsroom press releases insights blog research  intelligence innovation hub labs events about executive leadership corporate responsibility locations contact us privacy policy copyright  trademark careers people  culture university recruiting total rewards growth  learning 